FBIS3-56878 "drsov014_b_94025" FBIS-SOV-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Says Market Reforms to Continue LD2001155494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1506 GMT 20 Jan 94 LD2001155494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By BUSINESS-TASS] [Text] Moscow, 20 Jan--In an interview with an ITAR-TASS correspondent today, Aleksandr Shokhin, whose appointment as Russian Federation economics minister was also announced today, stated his determination to continue the market reforms. Shokhin expressed the hope that he would have sufficient levers of power to continue the policies of market reform. Shokhin is the fifth economics minister since Russia started its radical economic reforms in January 1992.
